p: Elevated temperature increased the rate of germling growth by 15.6% (main effect in the 3-way ANOVA, p = 0.035, Fig 5B). This increase was, however, more evident under low irradiance conditions, specifically in the control and high pCO 2 levels (ANOVA, p = 0.029 and 0.067, respectively) ( S4 Table). Germling growth rate increased by 70% from ambient to high temperature under control pCO 2, and by 57% under high pCO 2 ( Fig 5E).
